│ Looking at the issue more carefully, I need to understand the exact         │
│ problem. The bug occurs because LCSSA is not properly maintaining SCEV      │
│ information when ScalarEvolution is not available. However, my initial fix  │
│ of changing `getCachedResult` to `getResult` might not be the right         │
│ approach because it forces ScalarEvolution to be computed even when it      │
│ might not be needed.                                                        │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me look at the LCSSAWrapperPass implementation to see how it handles    │
│ ScalarEvolution:                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ ```cpp                                                                      │
│ bool LCSSAWrapperPass::runOnFunction(Function &F) {                         │
│   LI = &getAnalysis<LoopInfoWrapperPass>().getLoopInfo();                   │
│   DT = &getAnalysis<DominatorTreeWrapperPass>().getDomTree();               │
│   auto *SEWP = getAnalysisIfAvailable<ScalarEvolutionWrapperPass>();        │
│   SE = SEWP ? &SEWP->getSE() : nullptr;                                     │
│                                                                             │
│   return formLCSSAOnAllLoops(LI, *DT, SE);                                  │
│ }                                                                           │
│ ```                                                                         │
│                                                                             │
│ The wrapper pass uses `getAnalysisIfAvailable`, which is the correct        │
│ approach - it only gets ScalarEvolution if it's already available.          │
│                                                                             │
│ For the new pass manager version (`LCSSAPass::run`), it should follow the   │
│ same pattern. However, in the new pass manager, `getCachedResult` returns   │
│ null if the analysis hasn't been run, which is equivalent to                │
│ `getAnalysisIfAvailable` in the old pass manager.                           │
│                                                                             │
│ The real issue might be that when `indvars` runs, it expects LCSSA to have  │
│ been run with ScalarEvolution available, but the pass pipeline isn't        │
│ ensuring that.                                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me check what the actual problem is by looking at the test case more    │
│ carefully. The issue is that the zext instruction `%ext = zext i16 %add to  │
│ i32` should evaluate to 65512 (0xffe8), but it's returning 131048           │
│ (0x1ffe8). The difference is exactly 65536 (2^16), which suggests that the  │
